  <div class="timeline">
    <div class="timeline__item">
      <div class="timeline__period">2009 to 2013</div>
      <h3 class="timeline__role">Product Manager, Blackboard</h3>
      <p>Started my career proving UX moves revenue. Shipped 84 mobile apps, drove a 64% year-over-year
      jump in sales, and helped build the case that led to the company's acquisition.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline__item">
      <div class="timeline__period">2012 to 2017</div>
      <h3 class="timeline__role">PhD Researcher, Virginia Tech, alongside IBM and Amazon/Sonos</h3>
      <p>Pursued a PhD in Industrial &amp; Systems Engineering while running full industry roles at the
      same time: product management at IBM, scaling SaaS adoption 75x, then UX research for Amazon Echo
      and Sonos Play:5, concurrently. Selected as an NSF I-Corps Graduate Fellow.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline__item">
      <div class="timeline__period">2014 to 2017</div>
      <h3 class="timeline__role">Senior Product Manager, Joint Special Operations Command</h3>
      <p>A fourth concurrent thread during the PhD years: product strategy for UX and mobile innovation
      inside a defense command. Built the business case from scratch, secured $750K in research funding,
      and shipped two prototypes on time and under budget.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline__item">
      <div class="timeline__period">2018 to 2020</div>
      <h3 class="timeline__role">Lab Director &amp; Visiting Professor, Brigham Young University</h3>
      <p>Founded a university innovation lab from zero. Raised $325K, mentored 200+ students through
      AR/VR and mobile product delivery, and taught across Mixed Reality, HCI, and UX.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline__item">
      <div class="timeline__period">2018 to 2026</div>
      <h3 class="timeline__role">Senior Technical Product Manager to Principal AI Product Strategist, BluePath Labs</h3>
      <p>Eight years at a defense technology contractor. Directed a $45M portfolio across six government
      contracts, authored proposals worth $51B in potential contract value, led AI/LLM research at the
      Army Cybersecurity Institute, and scaled the team from 4 to 12 while doubling contract value.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline__item">
      <div class="timeline__period">2026 to Present</div>
      <h3 class="timeline__role">Senior Technology Solutions Strategist, Large Public Institution</h3>
      <p>Scaling from 1 to 4 concurrent AI programs and architecting the institutional platform spec that
      unifies them, from vendor evaluation through architecture-lock.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
